svg.title: Ember Core Concepts
svg.desc: This image presents four core concepts of an Ember app, the router, route handlers, templates, and components. The router, defined in router.js, maps a URL to an Ember Route. Every Ember Route has a route handler, which loads a template and a model. The model persists to a web server. The Route's template, finally, loads components and accesses the model data to populate the components' templates. This process is described in more detail below.
